Each seller i is associated with exactly one good Ai, for which she has true valuation ci which expresses the price at which it is beneficial for her to sell the good.
Negotiation-Range Mechanism: A  mechanism that computes a ZOPA, (L, H), for each matched buyer and seller in Tâˆ— , and provides the buyer with the upper bound H and the seller with the lower bound L. The basic assumption is that participants in the auction are self-interested players.
The utility for a buyer who does not participate in the trade is 0.
